metadata.name: The Warning
metadata.description:
you come across a weary, rusted sign, and begin to remark how it clearly has seen better days -- then stop midsentence as you draw near.

better days are hard to imagine; the sign's builders must have been in a hurry -- it seems to have been hammered together haphazardly, and no warning has been etched.

but then, there's that buzzing again, speaking to you of warnings in a new c0de:
